ingredientsDesc:
A. Calcitonin Standards: (Lyophilized)
One vial, labeled A, containing 0 pg/mL and five vials, labeled B-F, conaining concentrations of approximately 25, 100, 200, 500 and 1000 pg/mL (7.2-290.0) synthetic human calcitonin in buffer containing protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative. 
B. Ca;citonin [I-125] Reagent: (Lyophilized) (YELLOW)
One vial, containing <5 μCi (185 kBq) of [i-125]-labeled human synthetic calctionin in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.
C. Calcitonin antiserum: (Lyophilized) (BLUE)
One vial, containing goat anti-human calcitonin serum in a buffer with a protein stabilizer and sodium azide as a preservative.
D. Precipitating Reagent: (GREEN)
One bottle, 100 mL, containing donkey anti-goat gamma globulin, with polyethylene glycol as a precipitating did, and sodium azide as a preservative. 
E. Calcitonin Controls: (Lyophilized)
Two vials, levels i and II, containing low and high concentrations of calcitonin with sodium azides as a pre
